social_posts.post_text: 7th Annual Dockfest… just a gathering of neighbors on the lake having a jam session reminiscent of college- but our own grown up version. 🎸 It’s magic!  Thanks to all who make this day such FUN for everyone!  Back home now.  Until next year 🦄

Happiest first birthday to our firecracker baby girl- June Grace aka June bug!  What a wonderful addition to our family. She is our second grandchild and first girl… I am GiGi and Chris, my husband is Grandaddy 🫶🏼we love playing with them and watching them grow and change. She’s long and lean and about to walk on her own.  We sure do love life with you sweet girl!  You can find us in the pool today in ‘Hotlanta’ and out on the boat! 
Happy 4th to you all and stay safe! ❤️💙🤍🇺🇸🇺🇸

Few homes have captured my heart for as many years now as Casa de Campo, the home of Oscar de la Renta in the Dominican Republic.  I’ve had the first picture of the dining room in my inspiration photos forever it seems. Looking back on them again while trying to delete old pictures, I am reminded that my taste in his aesthetic has not veered at all. I’m still in love with this home after all these years… he said of this home ‘Every home should be welcoming, an oasis’. I couldn’t agree more Mr. De la Renta!🌴🌴

Hi friends. Happy Tuesday!  I wanted to share this moment on our back porch which was used rather extensively since last Thursday when a horrendous storm rolled through and left us without power for several days (powerless feeling too 🥹). I had this pretty lamp in the basement and thought about a @jamestfarmer picture I’ve admired for years of a giant porch he beautifully designed in Cashiers…  scroll to see that fabulousness here.  So I’ve been eying this fun little lampshade from @ballarddesigns and finally took the plunge and ordered her.  I also ordered rechargeable lightbulbs from Amazon since there is no outlet on that wall.  You never have an outlet exactly where you need them outside, right?! Anyway it’s so cozy out there now with this lamp and candlelight!  I love shopping in my own home. It’s so rewarding!  Oh and in the video seen here you can hear chippers grinding in the background.  Yes that is our new nature call here on the lake.  So many giant old trees fell during that storm, crushing homes and cars.  Yet, praise God, no one was hurt.  My heart aches for all who are dealing with the aftermath.  Mother Nature can be so scary.  Thank goodness for basements in our neck of the woods. 
Have a lovely week friend and happy shopping in your own home 🥰
🌴 Leslie

When building Palm House I knew I wanted to use ‘Persepolis’ by @quadrillefabrics ever since I saw Tory Burch’s iconic sunroom wallpapered with it.  It’s bold and makes a statement. Yet at night it feels something of a cocoon in it’s enveloping pattern play.  I’m having a large lumbar made now in a Schumacher leopard print for the bed.  Though I’d love a really cool chandelier like something from Madegoods, we seriously like a fast moving fan at this stage in life!  Turn the thermostat to 65 at night please and thank you ☺️ The views can’t be beat too.  Before I had custom shades in the windows, we could see the red light down lake about 5 miles away flashing on and off. Rather Gatsby I thought! 
Happy first day of August friends- Rabbit Rabbit for good luck!! We still have the rumble of chippers grinding all the downed trees.  Such a shame but it’s Mother Nature…❤️❤️

Today I celebrate another joyful year around the sun!  67 used to sound old!  What I know for sure is that it’s a number- just a mindset and I’m making sure I play and stay active every single day!  I workout daily and close all 3 rings too.  Starting a new 4 week challenge Monday with @trainwithjoan !! Looking forward to a new exercise routine besides my usual classes!  I’ve also found a new passion- gardening!🫑🫛 🌻 I find tremendous peace and joy tending to my “babies”! And then there is the other thing- grandbabies. Such fun with those precious angels! 
Today we went to our favorite lake restaurant and watched the boats come and go at the Annual Poker Run on Lake Lanier!  Dressed up as pirates they are all out having a great time in their tricked out boats.  And our trip with the kids to my happy place- #seaisland 🌴🩵 September you are a very special month for this girl! 
Enjoy your September too…
Love 🩵 Leslie
The doors are open. Welcome Fall and cooler temps!  My husband stays home on Fridays so we can take the boat to lunch on the lake.  Lake life is just so good 😎

Welcome to #palmhouse beautiful Zebra!  @polished_bypj posted this pretty picture of him and it was love at first sight!  PJ is so wonderful to work with but you have to be fast. Her treasures are snapped up so fast… but this time I scored!
Happy hunting and happy Monday❤️
Leslie 🌴🩵

Fall in the Deep South… just glorious 💕  We finished our bible study just yesterday. It was Bob Goff’s book ‘Undistracted’. It was so pertinent to us girls on my street who form our bible study.  We all discovered, through Bob’s stories and teachings, ways to undistract ourselves in our daily lives, and to focus on others and their needs. My son was also reading the book (Hendley) and we’d talk in the afternoons on my walks (via phone) discussing our thoughts about the book.  On Tuesday this week he informed me that he had picked up the phone and called Bob in San Diego… and guess what?! Bob answered the call!  They had a wonderful conversation and ended with Bob saying he’d come white water rafting with him next spring on the Ocoee River when Hendley gets home from New Zealand where is is a rafting guide. You see Bob puts his number in the back of all his books and encourages his readers to call him. How awesome is he?! So next week when we gather at my home for a prayer breakfast, we are going to try to call Bob too and invite him to Lake Lanier to go sailing on the lake with us (he’s a sailor). I wonder if he would join in?! That would be such a highlight to us girls. 
Happy Friday!  I hope you find a special surprise like this one!  I love love the goodness and kindness in people!  We need to spotlight the good more… there isn’t enough of this in our world.  I thank God for @bobgoff and his special book.  And for each of you too.
❤️🌴 Leslie

Wow!! Yesterday I had an experience that made my day. God’s plans are not ours… I was getting ready for our end of the season bible study breakfast at our house. I was heading out to try to find napkins to go with the decor of the table. I had a call from my husband that one of the guys on the street sent a text blast that a black lab was in his yard loose. My hubby asked me “Do you think you know who the pup is!? “ I sent out a text to all the gals in our neighborhood that this dog is loose  with a bright orange shock collar. Fast forward. I am in my SUV driving to get napkins for the Bible study breakfast. I get 4 houses down and there she is. Directly in front of me- Clearly not street wise 🥹 so I, the concerned dog Mom, put the car in park and jumped out to see what’s up with this confused pup.  She comes up wagging her entire body, tongue hanging out.  So sweet. What does she do?! She hops up into the passenger seat!!! OK well obviously she’s used to being a shotgun girl!! At this point no way am I leaving her out in the street (even though we are on a side street) so I drove home.  With her shotgun, excited to see where we are going!  Napkin plans dashed. Who cares. Sweet Labrador is scared and needs help. I put her in my fenced backyard and didn’t tell my pup Louie about my new visitor!  I sent photos of her to the girls on the street and they jumped into action!  One neighbor placed a photo of her on Facebook… and within 35 minutes I was contacted by a friend that the owner was on the street looking for her having seen the post.  The beautiful news is she got her master back and I was just so happy!  You can see in the reel that my napkins don’t match 😉but more importantly , ‘Rosie’ made it home safely!  I’ll get napkins someday. But for now, Rosie the lab is home with her owners. And I found out he is a policeman.  Thank you Rosie for reminding me that napkins that match is not as important as a beautiful dogs life. Scroll to see Rosie so happy in my car. She honestly just jumped in and waited for me to drive her somewhere fun. Don’t you just love God”s agenda over yours?! ❤️🐶❤️

Sharing some of my favorite live-in clothes… this is not my comfort zone!! Haha I am being encouraged by my girls (bosses😜) at @shopyourlikes to post myself in what I wear.  Really wear. Daily.  Here you go!! Links will be posted in my stories!  And by the way, any money made, which is small and goes to our charity we support so fully- @nolongerbound1.  Please follow them. My husband and I love this nonprofit. They truly turn the addicted and failing lives of men and their families into miracle success stories. We know many of the men. It’s the most beautiful blessing to observe and be a small part of it. 
So if you see me posting things like myself on stories, so far out of my comfort place, just know it’s for a good cause!!
Happy hump day and love from me❤️❤️
By the way for those asking, all Links to clothes etc will be in my Stories that day!
Happy 65th birthday to my best friend, my ❤️ You are so easy to Love!! Celebrating you all weekend! 🎁💃

Palm House all dressed up for Christmas!  I shortchanged her this year. Only about 1/2 of our decorations are on display- perhaps less!  You see, I got sick before Thanksgiving and what started as RSV moved into my lungs and took me to a place and pace not in my customary high speed go go go personality.  The doctor told me to rest, drink water and take some heavy duty meds to get past the illness.  What I’ve learned is magnanimous to me in my busy life.  Slow down.  Leslie- slow down.  I felt bad enough to heed the doctor’s orders- my husbands as well. I read. One book in particular sparked my interest and intentions. It’s called ‘The Well-Gardened Mind’ by Sue Stuart-Smith.  I already adore gardening. I feel like I have babies I need to care for- nurture… it’s natural to me and being an empty nester, fulfills that unresolved desire to be needed.  Albeit plants, not humans!  So in this book, and she’s a psychoanalyst, Sue discusses the mental benefits of gardening.  I knew it- that’s why I’m so calm and relaxed, listening to my music , gardening among the birds and butterflies. I’m seriously loving having enough land to have numerous outdoor rooms to create. But I digress. My illness gave me some insight into my need to work.  The realization that my new job looks different now and it doesn’t involve earning money, but rather toiling in the dirt for a different reward. Just as tangible but perhaps a more fulfilling life experience now. And at 67 I’m still planning to thrive in my health (once I get fully restored) and charity work.  And nurturing my faith. But I’m telling you I feel free.  Go garden, be well.  Peace be with you.  And do you know, God is right there among all the perfect growing things.  Of course He is!❤️
Merry Christmas from our family to you!❤️
